import cv2
import numpy as np

frame = np.zeros((240, 320, 3), np.uint8)
window = "Test Window"

def show_window(window, frame):
    print(cv2.getWindowProperty(window, cv2.WND_PROP_TOPMOST))
    while(True):
        cv2.imshow(window, frame)
        if cv2.waitKey() > 0:
            break

cv2.namedWindow(window)

cv2.setWindowProperty(window, cv2.WND_PROP_TOPMOST, 1)
show_window(window, frame)

cv2.setWindowProperty(window, cv2.WND_PROP_TOPMOST, 0)
show_window(window, frame)

import PyPDF2

def rotate_even_pages(input_pdf, output_pdf):
    # Open the input PDF
    with open(input_pdf, 'rb') as infile:
        reader = PyPDF2.PdfReader(infile)
        writer = PyPDF2.PdfWriter()
        
        # Iterate over all the pages
        num_pages = len(reader.pages)
        for i in range(num_pages):
            page = reader.pages[i]
            # Rotate only the even pages (index 1, 3, 5, etc.)
            if i % 2 == 1:  # 1-based index for even pages: 2, 4, 6, etc.
                page.rotate(180)
            writer.add_page(page)
        
        # Write the output PDF
        with open(output_pdf, 'wb') as outfile:
            writer.write(outfile)

# Example usage
input_pdf = 'input.pdf'  # Replace with your input PDF file
output_pdf = 'output.pdf'  # Replace with your desired output PDF file
rotate_even_pages(input_pdf, output_pdf)

print(f"Processed PDF saved as '{output_pdf}'")

#include "windows.bi"

type NET_API_STATUS as dword

#define _in
#define _out

const MAX_PREFERRED_LENGTH = -1
const cFILTER = 0
const pwServerName = NULL

enum UserType  
  USER_PRIV_GUEST
  USER_PRIV_USER
  USER_PRIV_ADMIN
  USER_PRIV_MAX
end enum

type USER_INFO_0
  as LPWSTR usri0_name  
end type
type USER_INFO_1
  as LPWSTR usri1_name
  as LPWSTR usri1_password
  as DWORD  usri1_password_age
  as DWORD  usri1_priv
  as LPWSTR usri1_home_dir
  as LPWSTR usri1_comment
  as DWORD  usri1_flags
  as LPWSTR usri1_script_path
end type
type USER_INFO_4
  as LPWSTR usri4_name
  as LPWSTR usri4_password
  as DWORD  usri4_password_age
  as DWORD  usri4_priv
  as LPWSTR usri4_home_dir
  as LPWSTR usri4_comment
  as DWORD  usri4_flags
  as LPWSTR usri4_script_path
  as DWORD  usri4_auth_flags
  as LPWSTR usri4_full_name
  as LPWSTR usri4_usr_comment
  as LPWSTR usri4_parms
  as LPWSTR usri4_workstations
  as DWORD  usri4_last_logon
  as DWORD  usri4_last_logoff
  as DWORD  usri4_acct_expires
  as DWORD  usri4_max_storage
  as DWORD  usri4_units_per_week
  as PBYTE  usri4_logon_hours
  as DWORD  usri4_bad_pw_count
  as DWORD  usri4_num_logons
  as LPWSTR usri4_logon_server
  as DWORD  usri4_country_code
  as DWORD  usri4_code_page
  as PSID   usri4_user_sid
  as DWORD  usri4_primary_group_id
  as LPWSTR usri4_profile
  as LPWSTR usri4_home_dir_drive
  as DWORD  usri4_password_expired
end type

dim fnNetUserEnum as function ( _
  _in      servername    as LPCWSTR     , _
  _in      level         as DWORD       , _
  _in      filter        as DWORD       , _
  _out     bufptr        as LPBYTE ptr  , _
  _in      prefmaxlen    as DWORD       , _
  _out     entriesread   as LPDWORD     , _
  _out     totalentries  as LPDWORD     , _
  _in _out resume_handle as PDWORD      ) as NET_API_STATUS
rem ------------------------------------------------------
dim fnNetUserGetInfo as function ( _
  _in      servername as LPCWSTR     , _
  _in      username   as LPCWSTR     , _
  _in      level      as DWORD       , _
  _out     bufptr     as LPBYTE ptr ) as NET_API_STATUS
rem ------------------------------------------------------
dim fnNetApiBufferFree as function ( _
  _in      Buffer     as LPVOID ) as NET_API_STATUS
rem ------------------------------------------------------

var hNetapi = LoadLibrary("Netapi32.dll")
fnNetUserEnum      = cast(any ptr, GetProcAddress(hNetapi, "NetUserEnum"))
fnNetUserGetInfo   = cast(any ptr, GetProcAddress(hNetapi, "NetUserGetInfo"))
fnNetApiBufferFree = cast(any ptr, GetProcAddress(hNetapi, "NetApiBufferFree"))

dim fnConvertSidToStringSidA as function ( _
  _in      Sid       as PSID , _
  _out     StringSid as LPSTR ptr ) as winbool


var hAdvApi = LoadLibrary("Advapi32.dll")
fnConvertSidToStringSidA = cast(any ptr, GetProcAddress(hAdvApi, "ConvertSidToStringSidA"))

dim as USER_INFO_0 ptr ptAccount
dim as dword dwResumeHandle
dim as NET_API_STATUS iResu

locate ,1  : print "Name";
locate ,22 : print "Full Name";
locate ,33 : print "Sid";
locate ,44 : print "Type";
locate ,51 : print "Flags";
print

do

  dim as dword dwEntriesRead , dwEntriesTotal 
  iResu = fnNetUserEnum( pwServerName , 0 , cFILTER , cast(any ptr,@ptAccount) , _ 
    MAX_PREFERRED_LENGTH , @dwEntriesRead , @dwEntriesTotal , @dwResumeHandle )
  if iResu <> ERROR_MORE_DATA andalso iResu then
    print "Failed to enumerated: Error: " & iResu
    exit do
  end if
  
  for N as long = 0 to dwEntriesRead-1  
    dim as USER_INFO_4 ptr ptInfo
    var pwUser = ptAccount[N].usri0_name
    print "'";*pwUser;"'";
    var iR = fnNetUserGetInfo( pwServerName , pwUser , 4 , cast(any ptr,@ptInfo) )
    if iR then continue for
    locate ,22
    print "'"+*ptInfo->usri4_full_name+"'";
    
    dim as zstring ptr pzSID
    fnConvertSidToStringSidA( ptInfo->usri4_user_sid , @pzSID )
    if pzSID then       
      var sSid = *pzSID , iSid = instrrev(sSid,"-")      
      locate ,33 : print "'*"+mid(sSid,iSid)+"'";
      LocalFree(pzSID)
    end if
    
    locate ,44
    select case ptInfo->usri4_priv
    case USER_PRIV_GUEST : print "Guest";
    case USER_PRIV_USER  : print "User";
    case USER_PRIV_ADMIN : print "Admin";
    case else            : print "0x"+hex(ptInfo->usri4_priv);
    end select      
    
    dim as string sFlags(31) = { _
      "Script"    ,"Disabled"  ,"0x4"       ,"HomeReq"    , _ '       x
      "Lockout"   ,"NoPass"    ,"CantChg"   ,"CanCrypt"   , _ '      x0
      "Dup"       ,"Normal"    ,"0x400"     ,"Inter"      , _ '     x00
      "Work"      ,"Server"    ,"0x4000"    ,"0x8000"     , _ '    x000
      "WontExpire","Logon"     ,"Smart"     ,"Trusted"    , _ '   x0000
      "NoDelegate","OnlyDES"   ,"NoPre"     ,"Expired"    , _ '  x00000
      "TrAuthDel" ,"NoDataReq" ,"Partial"   ,"UseAES"     , _ ' x000000
      "0x10000000","0x20000000","0x40000000","0x80000000"  }  'x0000000
    rem ---------------------------------------------------------------
   
    locate ,51
    for N as long = 0 to 31
      if (ptInfo->usri4_flags and (1 shl N)) then print sFlags(N);" ";
    next N
    
    print 
    
    fnNetApiBufferFree( ptInfo )
    
  next N
  
  fnNetApiBufferFree( ptAccount )

loop while iResu = ERROR_MORE_DATA

sleep

title: humanoidSound.rbxm

-- humanoidSound.rbxm: https://create.roblox.com/store/asset/12221490/

-- util

function waitForChild(parent, childName)
	local child = parent:findFirstChild(childName)
	if child then return child end
	while true do
		child = parent.ChildAdded:wait()
		if child.Name==childName then return child end
	end
end

function newSound(id)
	local sound = Instance.new("Sound")
	sound.SoundId = id
	sound.archivable = false
	sound.Parent = script.Parent.Head
	return sound
end

-- declarations

local sDied = newSound("rbxasset://sounds/uuhhh.wav")
local sFallingDown = newSound("rbxasset://sounds/splat.wav")
local sFreeFalling = newSound("rbxasset://sounds/swoosh.wav")
local sGettingUp = newSound("rbxasset://sounds/hit.wav")
local sJumping = newSound("rbxasset://sounds/button.wav")
local sRunning = newSound("rbxasset://sounds/bfsl-minifigfoots1.mp3")
sRunning.Looped = true

local Figure = script.Parent
local Head = waitForChild(Figure, "Head")
local Humanoid = waitForChild(Figure, "Humanoid")

-- functions

function onDied()
	sDied:Play()
end

function onState(state, sound)
	if state then
		sound:Play()
	else
		sound:Pause()
	end
end

function onRunning(speed)
	if speed>0 then
		sRunning:Play()
	else
		sRunning:Pause()
	end
end

-- connect up

Humanoid.Died:connect(onDied)
Humanoid.Running:connect(onRunning)
Humanoid.Jumping:connect(function(state) onState(state, sJumping) end)
Humanoid.GettingUp:connect(function(state) onState(state, sGettingUp) end)
Humanoid.FreeFalling:connect(function(state) onState(state, sFreeFalling) end)
Humanoid.FallingDown:connect(function(state) onState(state, sFallingDown) end)
